      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:242px;\"><a href=\"/File:SekienMikoshi.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/SekienMikoshi.jpg/250px-SekienMikoshi.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"317\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/SekienMikoshi.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:SekienMikoshi.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikoshi-ny%C5%ABd%C5%8D\">Mikoshi-nyūdō</a>, specifically a <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miage-ny%C5%ABd%C5%8D\">Miage-nyūdō</a>, as portrayed by Toriyama</div></div></div>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toriyama_Sekien\">Toriyama Sekien</a> (鳥山 石燕, 1712 – September 22, 1788),<br />\nis the pen-name of Sano Toyofusa, an 18th-century Japanese scholar, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ky%C5%8Dka\">kyōka poet</a>, and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukiyo-e\">ukiyo-e</a> artist.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Links\">Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Category:Toriyama_Sekien&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Toriyama_Sekien\">Category:Toriyama Sekien - Wikimedia Commons</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228160836\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.069 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.